  "text": "Similarly, maximum reduction in TPC was seen in onion dried at 50 °C, whereas a lower reduction was seen when drying at 70 °C (52). According to Gupta et al. [CITATION_1] and Garau et al. (53) , who concluded that longer drying times would result in higher reduction of TPC in orange by-products, important losses of TPC at lower drying temperature could also be att ributed to the longer duration of drying.",
